alt_title: WGS84 - World Geodetic System 1984, used in GPS
Spherical Mercator, Google Maps, OpenStreetMap, Bing, ArcGIS, ESRI
alt_description: This is projected coordinate system used for rendering maps in Google Maps, OpenStreetMap, etc. For details see Tile system.
Some used this likely as a mistype of Spherical Mercator EPSG:3857 (mistype)

alt_title: Spherical Mercator (unofficial - used in open source projects / OSGEO)
alt_description:
The unofficial code for Spherical Mercator (Google Maps, OpenStreetMap, ..) system - used in OpenLayers and other open-source projects.

See the official coordinate system EPSG:3857

alt_title: Spherical Mercator (unofficial deprecated OSGEO / Tile Map Service)
alt_description: See the official coordinate system EPSG:3857
First used by ESRI, but then replaced by 102100 (equivalent, deprecated)
Built differently, but equivalent to 102113 (equivalent, deprecated)

alt_title: Spherical Mercator (deprecated EPSG code wrongly defined)
alt_description: Deprecated EPSG code for Spherical Mercator - wrong definition similiar to how deprecated ESRI:102113 is defined
S-JTSK_Krovak_East_North: Used in ArcGIS and other ESRI products.
